# Qt coding style (Phase 12 cleanup). A thin profile on top of the
# upstream "Qt" preset. Invoke `clang-format -i <file>` to normalise
# anything you touch; Phase 12 intentionally does not sweep the tree
# wholesale because a per-file reformat would bury the substantive
# shim-removal diff. The profile lines below just pin choices where
# the Qt preset would otherwise differ from the habits this tree
# already carries (pointer alignment, tab vs space, column cap).

BasedOnStyle: Qt
Language: Cpp
Standard: c++17

IndentWidth: 4
TabWidth: 4
UseTab: Never

PointerAlignment: Left
SpaceAfterCStyleCast: false
SpaceBeforeParens: ControlStatements
ColumnLimit: 100

AllowShortFunctionsOnASingleLine: Empty
AllowShortIfStatementsOnASingleLine: Never
AllowShortLoopsOnASingleLine: false
